cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.MM, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the problem of estimating a latent signal from a lossy compressed version of the data, which involves concepts from information theory, machine learning, and signal processing. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses transportation-cost inequalities and properties of source codes, which are related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper evaluates the RD risk in special cases under different settings, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
